<TITLE> Police press charges against Babar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 24 (bdnews24.com)  The Gulshan police Sunday pressed charges against former state minister for home Lutfozzaman Babar in a case for illegal possession of firearms and ammunition. Sub-inspector Mohammad Khabir Ahmed of Gulshan Police Station, who is investigating the case, submitted turned in charge sheet to Chief Metropolitan Magistrates Court for Dhaka. S Sixteen people have been made prosecution witnesses in the case filed by SI Helal Uddin of Gulshan Police Station on June 3 under the Arms Act. He alleged Babar was in possession of one Brazil-made revolver, one shotgun, one rifle, one pistol, two magazines and 297 bullets but had no papers to justify his having the revolver. The joint forces on May 28 seized the arms in a raid on Babar's Gulshan home. bdnews
